SIMPLE: unchristian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unchristian
<hw>Un*chris"tian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>Christian</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
Christian; not converted to the Christian faith; infidel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contrary to Christianity; not like or becoming a
Christian; <as>as, <ex>unchristian</ex> conduct</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unchristian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unchristian
<hw>Un*chris"tian</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref. <ets>un-</ets>
+ <ets>Christian</ets>.]</ety> <def>To make unchristian.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unchristianize</ent>⟦br⟧
